 dinner (fried chicken = greasy fingers), and I hear a knock at the door.  Since I was expecting UPS to be there around that time with a package, I shoot out of my chair, hurriedly wash my hands, and answer the door (not bothering to look through the peephole)...<br><br>...to find this sloppily-dressed college-aged guy standing at my door with a rag in one hand and a spray bottle of some kind of crap in the other.  He tries to stick his head inside the door, and when I block him, he asks me, &quot;Are you the lady of the house?&quot;  With a mouthful of chicken, I say &quot;Yeth.&quot;  (I was in the middle of dinner, and only expecting to have to sign for a package.  Whaddya expect?)  He looks at me strangely, and responds, &quot;Well, I hope I'm not bothering you.  Now, if I might ask...&quot;  I interrupt him, and try to close the door:  &quot;Well, we were just in the middle of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> dinner</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.&quot;  He edges closer.  &quot;Oh, dinner, nice!  As I was saying, might I ask what is the hardest item in your house to clean?&quot;  I give him my &quot;What the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> fuck</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->?&quot; look, and just spout out anything off of the top of my head:  &quot;Uh... the stove, I guess.&quot;  Then he presents his lovely spray bottle to me, and says, &quot;Well, what I'm selling cleans messes off stoves easily!  Here, I'll show you...&quot; and he proceeds to try to move past me and inside the house!  I block him, nearly close the door in his face, and say (<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> very</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> snidely, I might add), &quot;Yes, well, sorry, but I'd <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> like</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to finish my <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> dinner</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, if you don't mind.&quot;  The guy just stood there, almost shocked.  His only response was &quot;Oh, okay...&quot; and off he went.<br><br>I know that it's a side job for some people.  I know it's the main job for some other people.  But for Christ's sake, is it too much to ask to have some <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> respect</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> for the people you're soliciting?  I don't know about you, but I don't want to be bothered while I'm eating dinner, especially by someone selling some crap that I don't need.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :/ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":/"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><IMG SRC="http://home.swbell.net/sdspies/images/mustelasig.jpg" BORDER="0" WIDTH="216" HEIGHT="212" alt="Image courtesy The Ferret Company http://www.ferretcompany.com/"><br><b>Mustela Furo</b>, Gnome Defiler of the 58th Essence Emerald<br><b>Valencia Draconis</b>, Wood Elf Preserver of the 56th Foraged Vein Worm<br>Proud Member of <i>Mithril Web</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utellwar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TellWar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(2/13/02 11:08:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1704.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Door-to-door Salesmen</span><hr size=1> Also being a woman and if home alone... letting a &quot;salesman&quot; in can be <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> very bad</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Yes that was very rude and you wonder how they would of dealt with it if it happened to them. <p>Tell Lespartan<br>Warrior<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ut